y demonstrates that a focus on wealth can provide us with a fuller understanding of charity in Jewish thought and the larger world from which Judaism and Christianity emerged.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCharityxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 0aPovertyxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 0aWealthxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishz978311099291508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520386907?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520386907423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520386907/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099291-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022